<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5" bgcolor="#828282" class='forumpostcontent'>
  <tr>
    <td class='forumpostcontent'>Still fine tuning it but I was able to walk away from the keyboard an hour at a time with the below macro. After 4 hours, I sampled over 1000 of a gem I surveyed and went from Survey II to Survey III.<br />
<br />
-----------------<br />
/stand<br />
/sample<br />
/pause 300<br />
/stand<br />
/sit<br />
/pause 300<br />
-----------------<br />
<br />
This single set is 10 minutes.  Repeat it 6 times to get an hour of macro.  I'm still testing but you may be able to drop the second stand from the set.<br />
<br />
You also might want to time how long it takes for your green bar to go down and up while sitting.  Each race/profession will have different regen times and amounts of Action bar.<br />
<br />
One thing you don't want to do is start a second macro before the first has finished. To verify completion, you might want to add "/say ---ALL DONE---" to the end of the macro.<br><br>
        <!-- BEGIN TEMPLATE: postbit_signature -->
<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1"><br>
__________________<br>
<font color="crimson"><b>Sylk</b></font></smalfont>
