<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5" bgcolor="#6D6D6D" class='forumpostcontent'>
  <tr>
    <td class='forumpostcontent'>Woot!  I now have the perfect Sample macro.  There are basically 3 ways to make macros longer:<br />
<br />
1.  Add many lines of code to extend length.<br />
<br />
2.  Use the "/load" command to call a text file (macro1.txt for example).  This allows you to fine tune a complex macro and use the benefits of a real text editor in creation.<br />
<br />
3.  Create a simple 1-repitition macro and add a loop command to the end.<br />
<br />
Number 3 is by far the easiest and most efficient for simple macros like Sampling.<br />
<br />
Here is the code for my perfect Sample Macro:<br />
<br />
I'm Sampling (AFK)<br />
/stand<br />
/sample<br />
/pause 450<br />
/sit<br />
/pause 300<br />
/ui action toolbarSlot00<br />
<br />
The last command is the loop command.  It will run the first button on your hotkey bar. The hot key bar is numbered from 00 to 23.  If the macro is in your 12th hotkey slot, use "toolbarSlot11".<br />
<br />
To end the macro, just roll your toolbar slots up or down until a blank appears in the macro slot.  The running macro will run the blank slot as the next loop starts, thus breaking the loop.<br />
<br />
Adjust the pauses for sampling and sitting to match your action bar capability/requirements and you're set.  I was able to sample over 1700 of a mineral before either the servers went down or I was booted from inactivity(not sure which).<br><br>
        <!-- BEGIN TEMPLATE: postbit_signature -->
<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1"><br>
