<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
              <tr> 
                <td class="forumposttitle" width="100%"><img src="images/posticon.gif" border="0" alt="Old Post"> Automating Crafting</td>
                <td align="right" nowrap class="forumposterdate">&laquo; 
                  08-11-2003 08:30 PM &raquo;</td>
              </tr>
            </table>

<table cellpadding='0' cellspacing='0' border='0' width='100%'>
<tr>
<td bgcolor='#000000'><img src="/images/spacer.gif" alt="" width="1" height="1"></td>
</tr>
</table>

<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5" bgcolor="#6D6D6D" class='forumpostcontent'>
  <tr>
    <td class='forumpostcontent'><b><u>Prerequisites:</u><br />
<br />
3 Weapon, Droid, General Crafting Tools.<br />
A huge amount of resources. <br />
A good mouse button.<br />
A good finger to press it.<br />
<br />
<u>Notes:</u><br />
<br />
If you've never tried to macro a crafting session before, strap on your seatbelt and get ready to click. This is going to burn through your resources faster than anything you've ever seen before. <br />
<br />
The pauses in <font color="crimson">red</font> below are directly proportional to the creation time of the schematic. They will need to be adjusted accordingly when using different schematics. NEVER change the "/pause 2" commands.  They must remain static for the macro to work properly.<br />
<br />
The "/select 66" command in <font color="green">green</font> below determines which drafting schematic will be used. Number "66" is a Blaster Pistol Barrel. This is ideal when grinding from Novice to the first box. Barrels only require Steel as a resource and have 2 components to fill. (You want number 4, 5, or 6 when grinding from Artisan to Novice Weaponsmith, Armorsmith, Droidsmith, etc. These numbers are the CDEF weapons and will give you General Crafting experience.)<br />
<br />
<u>Known issues:</u><br />
<br />
You will notice what looks like a redundant line "/createPrototype".  Both are required.  Do not remove either of them.  The first one creates the prototype.  The second one forces the crafting window to close after the prototype is created (giving the text message "Crafting session ended").  It is a bug that the crafting window stays open and the redundant line is a work-a-round to fix it. Without this work-a-round, the next crafting session cannot start.<br />
<br />
For some reason, I cannot get "Practice" mode to stick. It used to stick but now it doesn't. This might be an issue specific to my own client. If you experience it too, you will need to halt the macro from time to time to empty your inventory. Even though "Practice" mode won't work for me, it is definitely worth using the macro.<br />
<br />
<u>Setup:</u><br />
<br />
1. Scroll up to an empty toolbar row<br />
2. Drag the 3 Crafting Tools to slot 1, 2, and 3<br />
3. Create the macro and drag it to slot 4<br />
4. (optional) Empty your inventory of all but the required resources and crafting tools.<br />
<br />
<u>Macro:</u><br />
<br />
/ui action toolbarSlot00<br />
<font color="green">/select 66</font><br />
<font color="crimson">/pause 4</font><br />
/nextCraftingStage<br />
/nextCraftingStage<br />
/createPrototype<br />
/createPrototype<br />
/pause 2<br />
/ui action toolbarSlot01<br />
<font color="green">/select 66</font><br />
<font color="crimson">/pause 4</font><br />
/nextCraftingStage<br />
/nextCraftingStage<br />
/createPrototype<br />
/createPrototype<br />
/pause 2<br />
/ui action toolbarSlot02<br />
<font color="green">/select 66</font><br />
<font color="crimson">/pause 4</font><br />
/nextCraftingStage<br />
/nextCraftingStage<br />
/createPrototype<br />
/createPrototype<br />
/pause 2<br />
/ui action toolbarSlot03<br />
<br />
<u>What to expect after I start the macro?</u><br />
<br />
This will start a loop that uses 3 crafting tools at once. You will need to pay attention and click fast to keep up with it.<br />
<br />
If anybody knows how to get "Practice" mode to stick, please post here :-)</b><br><br>
        <!-- BEGIN TEMPLATE: postbit_signature -->
<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1"><br>
__________________<br>
<font color="crimson"><b>Sylk</b></font></smalfont>
